Part 2: 
After Member A obtains submission ID Member B should log in and try to access the same submission ID (2880).

GET /diagnostics/api/medicaldata/forms/mq/submissions/2880/data
Host: stage-api.ezra.com
Cookie: session=memberB_session
https://stage-api.ezra.com/diagnostics/api/medicaldata/forms/mq/submissions/2880/data
and they shouldn't get 200 response. 


Step 1 — Valid access (Member A)

Member A logs in and loads their questionnaire.

GET /diagnostics/api/medicaldata/forms/mq/submissions/2880/data
Host: stage-api.ezra.com
Cookie: session=memberA_session

Expected result:

HTTP 200 OK

The API returns Member A’s questionnaire data.

Step 2 — Unauthorized access attempt (Member B)

Now Member B logs in and tries to access the same submission ID (2880).

GET /diagnostics/api/medicaldata/forms/mq/submissions/2880/data
Host: stage-api.ezra.com
Cookie: session=memberB_session

Expected result:

HTTP 403 Forbidden

or

HTTP 404 Not Found

The response must not return any medical questionnaire data.

One more test would be to increment the id (just in case): 
GET /diagnostics/api/medicaldata/forms/mq/submissions/2881/data

Expected result:

HTTP 403 or 404

This checks the API cannot be enumerated to discover other patients' questionnaires.

